ply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   pet power</span><hr size=1> Just wanting to know how some pets stack up.  Im lvl 33 now and was looking to see what lvl's pets get more powerfull than others.  ect ect.  More or less i just want to know the break down of the pets power.  <br>
whan <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=feakazoid>FEAKAZOID</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#333333>(3/1/03 2:39:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1010.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   The best numbers</span><hr size=1> Level 44 and 49(m lvl 45 but saw the lvl 49 pet in action) Level 44 is nice. Pets hit for up to 48 Focused and quad a bunch. Lvl 49 is very good. Pets hit for 56(I think) and are very good I hear. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tangting01>TangTing01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 198<br> <font color=#333333>(3/1/03 2:17:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1010.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The best numbers</span><hr size=1> Up to 34, I had used the water pet exclusively.  Post 34, I started using the fire pet and MSII.  At 39, I had basically shelved the water in favor of fire and air.  I found the air pet finally had the hps (combined with its agility) to be the best tank of the group.  I've never gotten much use from the earth pet - it takes a lot of damage.  I think you have to be a chain-caster to really appreciate it.  A big part of the equation is whether you have the pet focus items - Torch of Alna, Stein of Ulissa, Broom of Trilon, and Shovel of Ponz.  The increase in hps the Torch and Broom give the Fire and Air pets, respectively, makes a big difference. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zibleez>Zibleez</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(3/1/03 2:48:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1010.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: pet power</span><hr size=1> Don't underestimate the power of the earth pet and chain petting... While it still feels pretty cheap to me (I was a die hard pet healer/equipper and what not), the fact that you can pull with burst of flame and then let your pet beat on a mob until it's at ~20% health, then summon another for -200~ mana at level 50, which is the cost of our level 44 heal, well, the numbers just don't compare with nuking and what not.  But nuking's fun, so we'll still do it, of course.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Pets do scale up in power accordingly... the level right before new pets - 38, 43, 48 - are always painful, moreso because you know those new pets are around the corner than because of any actual difficulty.  Each Tier of pets certainly feels like an improvement over the last, and I've even seen a tangible difference between our focused 49 earth pet and the 51st level Vocerate: Earth.  Also, as you're getting to the point where your pets are getting enough hp, don't underestimate the power of your fire pet.  Their damage shield is something like their level +2, which is a ridiculously high number as you level up, and mobs beat themselves to death on your pet.  Ultimately, most mages I've talked to used the fire pet exclusively from level 34 to 49, since its damage shield is so powerful, and it hits pretty well too.  Air is great in groups or against casters thanks to its stunning ability, and water regenerates extremely fast, so if you want to use a pet to solo but leave yourself downtime between pulls, water pet will help preserve mana by regenerating it's hp while you med.  All in all, every pet has its own use, in its own situation, and all of them are equally useful.  The fire pet, however, becomes a real monster up to level 49, assuming it's taking hits.<br>
<br>
Now that I've rambled... back to work.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=594005">Zibleez Cinderflux</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=baisblackfingers>BaisBlackfingers</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#333333>(3/2/03 8:54:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1010.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Air</span><hr size=1> Also if you start getting into multi-mage groups, do not underestimate the power of the broom brigade!  2 air pets stunning can nearly match enchie/shammy slow, 3 can sometimes exceed it for damage mitigation.  4 is disturbing, but a hard group to make.  Make sure to malise so that all those stuns land. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eloinapyromancer>Eloina Pyromancer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 490<br> <font color=#333333>(3/3/03 5:27:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1010.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Air</span><hr size=1> With regards to chaincasting pets... it's an outstanding tactic once you're past level 44 or so.  Before that, you have better results nuking, in my experience.  Pets prior to level 44 just don't have the hitpoints to make the tactic worthwhile.<br>
<br>
Of course, it really comes into its own with the level 49 earth pet.  :-) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gunnosoke>Gunnosoke</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(3/5/03 4:16:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1010.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Air</span><hr size=1> Here is pet power - or not.  I am a 34 mage - but I also am a 62 Necro with Legacy of Zek pet.<br>
<br>
My pet dueled the lvl 65 Mage pet the other day.  The mage pet won - but only had 2 bubs of health left.  When my LoZ pet enraged - it really put a hurting on the Mage pet.  If I dueled a comparable lvl 62 mage with his pet - I think my necro pet would have won easily. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=414945" target="top"><br>
My Stuff</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
To seek out new life - where it has never been found before - to boldly go where no man has gone before - and KILL IT!!! </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lordgojirax>LordGojirax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 570<br> <font color=#333333>(3/5/03 8:28:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1010.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jackntracie.com/images/gojhead.jpg width=98 height=126></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Air</span><hr size=1> At level 34, the Mage pets gain a considerable boost (30-40hp per tick!) of HP regen too!<br>
<br>
It's so nice to end a fight and have your pet healthy by the time you engage in your next one. Much faster than before.<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.jackntracie.com/images/gojirax.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eloinapyromancer>Eloina Pyromancer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 504<br> <font color=#333333>(3/5/03 9:54:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1010.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Air</span><hr size=1> Actually, the regen boost happens at 39... or at least it did. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bolerusis>BolerusIS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(3/5/03 11:54:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1010.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Air</span><hr size=1> hi all<br>
<br>
I am a level 57 mage <br>
<br>
in my opinion Chain casting is a great way to go<br>
<br>
it can of course be a bit boring if you are purely chaining, I do tend to nuke as well, dependant on the situation I use the excellnt Scirroco (did i spell that right) - after malosi of course<br>
<br>
On a single target that does upto 1890 damage if the mob is unresistant to all 3 rains<br>
<br>
i also use my new shock of steel, at first i thought it was a bad upgrade (doesent do much more than char)  but to yet I have not had it resisted by the mobs i have been fighting (only been 57 for about 4 hours of play)<br>
<br>
Today I was bored and went to Rockhoppers to score a few pelt for that elusive tailoring increase.<br>
<br>
Most of the hoppers were light blue ( as expected ) with the occasional dark blue thrown in for good measure (about 1 in 10 were Dblue)<br>
<br>
Any way after about an hour, i pulled up my inventory to see how many pelts i had gained, and noticed that i had got a full blue of exp.<br>
<br>
I was a bit surprised, because that is about the same rate that I have been gettign exp when i have been fighting in Velks, for exp (if that made sense)<br>
<br>
So I checked it over the next blue, - 1 hour 15 minutes = 1 blue<br>
<br>
Most of the mobs, i just sat there and let my pet kill them.<br>
<br>
Point is:-<br>
<br>
Don't always discount the lower zones when you are soloing for exp<br>
<br>
much quicker kills with your great pets can sometimes make up for  the lower exp per kill ratio<br>
<br>
<br>
Bolerus  57th mage <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showPrevMessage?topicID=1010.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showNextMessage?topicID=1010.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1010.topic&index=9><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.threadControl?topicID=1010.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1010.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1010.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="themagicianstowerannouncements">Administration<option value="themagicianstowergeneral">General<option value="themagicianstowerfrm32">Class Balance<option value="themagicianstowerfrm45">User Interface<option value="themagicianstowerspells">Spells<option value="themagicianstowerequipmentandquests">Quests<option value="themagicianstowerfrm28">Equipment<option value="themagicianstowerfrm29">Magician Pets<option value="themagicianstowerfrm30"